about the elections because now we are democratic. Niger has become democratic after 20 years of a military regime.

BEC : Nigeria?

NE: Yes, Nigeria.

And other things? Trade.

BEC: Unfortunately, trade, the way you meant it, has not changed yet, but we really may have a trade relationship soon.

Any thoughts you’d like to leave us with?

It is actually hard [to leave comments] because I am really happy that Niger is now a democratic country and we really want to have that in Nigeria because our problem in Nigeria is that although Nigeria is a great country, we are not democratic and if we become a democratic country, it will really make a big, big difference. Niger has achieved that, and we have seen how the Niger citizens are responding to that, they are saying now they feel much better and they feel happy and they know they can speak. And on the other side, Nigeria is still suffering from military regime and if Niger has become democratic, so also Nigeria should become democratic. I really think this is a good thing.

DESIDERATA

“Desiderata” é uma palavra italiana que se relaciona com o latim. Quer dizer haver desejos ou anseios com o somatório de um ser belo, bom e feliz.
